  "texts": [
    "Taken together, these findings suggest that the low-rank space offers sufficient expressiveness, but the classical low-rank adapter formulation struggles to fully utilize this potential.",
    "Indeed, we observe comprehensive empirical evidence for this underutilization: when fine-tuning Llama-2-7B with LoRA, we find that the stable rank, a robust analogue of the matrix rank and Each pixel shows ∥ wiwj ∥ 2; rows and columns are rearranged to reveal cluster patterns in both plots.",
    "Emergence of a cluster pattern is evidence for DC.",
    "The algebraic rank is 32 for both methods, yet the stable rank is 1.06 and 5.49 for LoRA and PoLAR, respectively.",
    "See also Section 2.1."
  ]
